CHANGELOG.md:95:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:97:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins trackerŌåÆworldŌåÆdefault fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:107:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:121:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong ŌåÆ 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:163:- Wired sample auto-tagging into the capture write path: `sample_capture_daemon.py` now exposes a stdlib-only `save_capture()` helper that writes mono 24-bit WAV captures, emits contextual + acoustic tags via `build_sample_tags()`, and persists both flattened tag fields and JSON payloads into `index.sqlite`; `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` now covers room/contextual tag emission, sample-index persistence, and percussive contact-capture indexing.
CHANGELOG.md:178:- Added installation-aware acoustic ecology policies: new `acoustic_ecology.py` module provides `resolve_acoustic_ecology()` which translates presence, cadence, day phase, room activity, attention state, and dwell time into a frozen `AcousticEcologyPolicy` with hard ceilings for volume, onset density, and spectral brightness, silence window parameters, ordered source preferences, keynote privilege weights, and density/voice caps. Sleep and wind-down modes enforce non-negotiable ceilings that cannot be overridden by any modifier. Performance attention overrides wind-down constraints when the human is actively engaged. Room activity boosts keynote privilege so the room's own soundscape is the acoustic content.
CHANGELOG.md:211:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:216:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
CHANGELOG.md:219:- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
CHANGELOG.md:220:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:242:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:345:- Added an interactive startup wizard that asks onboarding questions one at a time.
CHANGELOG.md:346:- Added heuristic follow-up questions when startup answers are vague or underspecified.
CHANGELOG.md:348:- Added startup artifacts: `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, and `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`.
CHANGELOG.md:349:- Added agent roster customization and capability inference during startup.
