----\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+def verify_resolution(leader_notes: tuple[int, int], follower_notes: tuple[int, int]) -> bool:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    Verify resolution-completion for a single interval transition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    If the first vertical interval is a sharp dissonance, both voices\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    must move stepwise (0, 1, or 2 semitones) to resolve it.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    initial_interval = interval_between(leader_notes[0], follower_notes[0])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    if initial_interval.consonance != \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sharp_dissonance\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        return True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    leader_motion = abs(leader_notes[1] - leader_notes[0])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    follower_motion = abs(follower_notes[1] - follower_notes[0])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    return leader_motion <= 2 and follower_motion <= 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+def voice_leading_smoothness(leader_notes: tuple[int, ...], follower_notes: tuple[int, ...]) -> float:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    Calculate voice-leading smoothness scoring for a pair of voices.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    Returns the average size of leaps (in semitones) across all melodic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    intervals in both voices. A lower score means smoother voice-leading.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    total_motion = 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    intervals = 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    if len(leader_notes) > 1:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        total_motion += sum(abs(leader_notes[i] - leader_notes[i-1]) for i in range(1, len(leader_notes)))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        intervals += len(leader_notes) - 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    if len(follower_notes) > 1:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        total_motion += sum(abs(follower_notes[i] - follower_notes[i-1]) for i in range(1, len(follower_notes)))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        intervals += len(follower_notes) - 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    if intervals == 0:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        return 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    return float(total_motion) / intervals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/progress.md b/progress.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex c73f624..4e7b7b9 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/progress.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/progress.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -2,10 +2,10 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n Generated from SQLite state (`tasks`, `task_runs`, `escalations`). Do not edit manually.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-ETC: ~5h 6m remaining (15 tasks, low confidence, calibrating)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Expected completion: 3:09 PM today.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Progress: [Ō¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æ] 77%  49 / 64 tasks complete\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  completed: 49, pending: 15, blocked: 0, skipped: 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ETC: ~10h 34m remaining (47 tasks, low confidence, calibrating)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Expected completion: 11:47 PM today.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Progress: [Ō¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢łŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æŌ¢æ] 56%  60 / 107 tasks complete\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  completed: 60, pending: 45, needs_split: 2, blocked: 0, skipped: 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n - **T-001@20260408T223256Z**: complete ŌĆö Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n - **T-002@20260408T223256Z**: complete ŌĆö Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -57,18 +57,62 @@ Progre