# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 end-to-end accompaniment test coverage (frac-0055): `tests/test_accompaniment.py` now ships a new `TestAccompanimentEndToEnd` class that drives the existing Korsakov accompaniment public surface (`DensityTracker`, `select_accompaniment_type`, `breathing_swell`, `should_transition_gradually`, `should_pedal`, `pedal_note`, `get_pattern`, and the six pattern generators) through end-to-end multi-step pytest methods. The new tests sweep the documented density bands and verify the inverse-density rule, iterate every pattern type 1-6 to assert non-empty events with positive amps/releases, sweep `breathing_swell` over rest/active/edge inputs, walk full phrase boundaries through `should_pedal` + `pedal_note`, run the dense-melody and resting-melody pipelines end-to-end through a synthetic `DensityTracker` window, and pin a six-bar composer loop. A `test_test_accompaniment_reaches_depth_two` gate test asserts the file's fractal classification is at least depth 2. Existing `TestDensityTracker`, `TestSelectAccompanimentType`, `TestPatterns`, `TestPedalPoint`, `TestBreathing`, and `TestTransition` assertions are preserved unchanged; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain green.

- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.

- Added depth-2 test_genai smoke probe (frac-0053): root-level `test_genai.py` is now a typed module exposing a frozen `GenAIProbeResult` dataclass plus `create_genai_client`, `list_model_names`, `probe_genai_client`, `summarize_probe_result`, `format_probe_lines`, and `main` so callers, tests, and operator dashboards can drive `probe ŌåÆ summarize ŌåÆ render ŌåÆ main` without re-implementing the conditional script logic. The success path returns a populated result with the sampled model names; any raised `Exception` is folded into an `ok=False` result with the stringified error and zero models. `summarize_probe_result` is JSON-safe (`sampled_models` rendered as a list); `format_probe_lines` preserves the original CLI output format byte-for-byte ("Successfully created client without explicit API key." header plus per-model lines on success, single "Error: <error>" line on failure); `main()` runs the probe and prints each line, returning exit code 0 to match the original `python test_genai.py` smoke behavior. `tests/test_test_genai_depth.py` pins the new probe surface, client construction (explicit key + default-auth env), limit-respecting model sampling, success/error result paths, JSON-safe summary, canonical CLI line rendering, end-to-end main, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` and the startup identity anchors remain green.

- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw memory journal helpers (frac-0051): `promptclaw/memory.py` now exposes a frozen `MemoryEntry` dataclass plus typed helpers `format_run_block`, `parse_memory_log`, and `summarize_memory_log`, and `MemoryStore` gains `entries`, `latest_entry`, and `summary` read-side methods so callers and operator diagnostics can render a single run's memory block, parse the project memory file back into structured entries (run id, title, status, lead, verifier, final phase, body), and emit a JSON-safe aggregate (entry count, latest run id, sorted status counts, sorted lead-agent counts excluding the `n/a` placeholder). `MemoryStore.append_run_summary` now delegates block rendering to `format_run_block` so the on-disk markdown shape stays byte-identical for orchestrator clarification-pause and final-summary writes. `tests/test_promptclaw_memory_depth.py` pins canonical block layout, `n/a` agent fallbacks, append/parse round-trip, empty-input handling, JSON-safe summary aggregation, `n/a` lead exclusion, store read helpers (including missing-file path), and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` remains the regression anchor for end-to-end run behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.

- Added depth-2 image API schema summaries (frac-0050): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/schemas.py` now exposes `TERMINAL_JOB_STATUSES`, `ACTIVE_JOB_STATUSES`, frozen `JobLifecycleSummary` and `InternalSpecProfile` dataclasses, and typed helpers `is_terminal_status`, `build_job_lifecycle_summary`, `summarize_status_response`, `build_internal_spec_profile`, and `summarize_internal_spec`. The helpers give operator logs and dashboards JSON-safe lifecycle/spec metadata including terminal-state classification, output counts, error flags, image dimensions, pixel count, megapixels, prompt previews, style presence, model overrides, and content-piece IDs without changing any Pydantic request/response fields or runtime behavior. `tests/test_image_api_schemas_depth.py` pins the new helper surface and fractal depth >= 2; existing parser, worker, app, jobs DB, S3 uploader, startup identity, and narrative ASGI startup anchors remain green.

- Added depth-2 image API S3 uploader reports (frac-0049): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/s3_uploader.py` now exposes module-level `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL`, `DEFAULT_CONTENT_TYPE`, and `CONTENT_TYPE_BY_EXTENSION` constants plus a frozen `UploadReport` dataclass and typed helpers `guess_content_type`, `categorize_upload_size`, `build_upload_report`, `summarize_upload`, and `summarize_upload_report` so worker batches and operator dashboards can map filenames to canonical MIME types, aggregate `UploadResult` records into bucket / object-count / total-bytes / keys / urls reports, classify byte sizes into empty/small/medium/large bands, and emit JSON-safe per-result and per-batch summaries. `upload_image` keeps its keyword-only signature, single `put_object` call, and direct-S3 URL contract; the cache-control header is now sourced from `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL` rather than a literal. `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py` pins MIME classification (known + unknown + missing suffix), batch aggregation, empty-iterable handling, size-band thresholds, JSON-safe summaries, the cache-header contract, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py` remains the regression anchor for existing upload behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw scaffold template reports (frac-0048): `promptclaw/templates.py` now exposes frozen `ScaffoldTemplateEntry` and `ScaffoldTemplateReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `template_category`, `required_startup_prompt_paths`, `scaffold_template_entries`, `scaffold_template_report`, and `summarize_scaffold_templates` so callers can inspect generated starter scaffold files by category, byte size, required startup prompt coverage, and JSON-safe per-entry rows. Existing `project_scaffold(project_name)` output is preserved exactly for bootstrap and CLI init consumers. `tests/test_promptclaw_templates_depth.py` pins category classification, scaffold contract preservation, report totals/category counts, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; bootstrap/config/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw config status reports (frac-0046): `promptclaw/config.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigStatusReport` plus typed helpers `enabled_agents`, `config_status_report`, `summarize_config`, and `load_or_default` so callers can inspect the project name, artifact root, control-plane mode/agent, default task type, agent count, sorted enabled/disabled agent name tuples, and validation issues in one diagnostic call. `enabled_agents` returns deterministic alphabetical names; `summarize_config` is JSON-safe and exposes lists rather than tuples; `load_or_default` returns the persisted config when `promptclaw.json` is present and otherwise returns `default_project_config(project_name)` without writing to disk. Existing `default_project_config`, `config_path`, `load_config`, `save_config`, and `validate_config` signatures and behavior are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_config_depth.py` pins enabled-agent ordering, default and invalid-config status reports, JSON-safe summary lists, the load-or-default branch, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_config.py` remains the regression anchor for existing load/validate behavior.

- Added depth-2 composer quote verification reports (frac-0045): `my-claw/tools/composer_quote_verify.py` now exposes a frozen `QuoteVerificationReport` plus typed helpers `build_quote_verification_report`, `summarize_quote_verification_report`, `render_quote_verification_lines`, and `quote_verification_exit_code` around the existing hardware-free known-room/self-quote smoke path. The report captures descriptor identity/tags, requested/captured piece counts, song ids, match details, overlap, score, and status while preserving `trigger_composer_pieces`, `find_motif_tag_match`, and the CLI's existing success/failure output and exit codes. `tests/test_composer_quote_verify_depth.py` pins the end-to-end report, JSON-safe summary, CLI line rendering, failure-status exit mapping, and fractal depth >= 2; original composer quote, sample capture, self-listener, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.


